Members. The governing body of the Trust shall be a Board of Trustees composed of nine (9) members, none of whom shall be employees of the Miami-Dade County. The members shall be the following:


One (1) member representing the financial or investment banking community;



One (1) member nominated by the Chairperson of the Board of County Commissioner's Committee which has jurisdiction over housing and community and economic development;



One (1) member with a background in public sector budgeting and finance;



One (1) member nominated by the Metro-Miami Action Plan Trust;



One (1) member nominated by the Dade Affordable Housing Advisory Board;



One (1) member nominated by Miami-Dade Housing Finance Authority;



One (1) member representing the non-profit developer community;



One (1) member representing the insurance community; and



One (1) member from the private home builders community.
The Chair of the Board of the County Commissioners shall contact each of the entities referenced in Section 17-133 (1) to obtain the names of interested and eligible persons and their resumes. The Chair shall obtain a pool of no less than three (3) names of candidates per seat on the Trust. Upon receipt of the names all candidates, the Chair shall forward them by resolution to the Board of County Commissioners. From the pool of candidates for each seat, the Board of County Commissioners shall appoint one (1) eligible person to serve as a member of the Board of Trustees.
Individuals shall be appointed based on the following criteria:


Knowledge of and demonstrable service to the affordable housing community;



Representation of the diverse populations of the Miami-Dade County community, including the proportional representation of women; and



Special expertise in affordable housing.

Members of the Trust shall serve without compensation but shall be entitled to reimbursement for necessary expenses incurred in the discharge of their duties.
